# Day 1 - Basics

## What is Internet
Internet is a global network that connects millions of devices and allows communication.

## IP Address
IP Address is a unique identifier for a device on a network.
Example: 192.168.1.1

## Types of IP
- Private IP (used inside local network)
- Public IP (used on internet)

## DNS (Domain Name System)
DNS converts domain names into IP addresses.
Example: google.com → IP address
